overview: The user initiated a request to fix a pull request for a sleep
  questionnaire application, citing numerous issues and failing Vercel deploys.
  The agent began by diagnosing the build failures and reviewing the
  comprehensive list of issues provided by a Cursor bot. It was discovered that
  some lint errors, initially reported by CI, were already resolved locally. The
  agent then systematically addressed the remaining critical issues. This
  included overhauling the admin authentication to use a secure HMAC-based
  session system, validating and capping pagination parameters in API routes to
  prevent abuse, and implementing pagination for CSV exports to avoid memory
  exhaustion. Furthermore, the PDF generation logic was refined to correctly
  handle empty time inputs and accurately calculate sleep metrics by including
  minutes. User experience was improved by allowing number input fields to
  accept null values and by activating the "Download PDF" button. Finally, a
  hardcoded "Test User" in PDF reports was replaced with a generic "Patient"
  label. The overall outcome was a more secure, stable, and functional
  application.
